unexpected ways in which they worked to bring the Saints into the nation’s mainstream after the scandal of polygamy. Engaging, interdisciplinary, and deeply researched, Charles Ellis Johnson and the Erotic Mormon Image demonstrates the profound role pictures played in the creation of both the modern Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints and the modern American nation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMormons in art. 0aPolygamy - Religious aspects - Mormons. 0aPolygamyxReligious aspectsxMormons. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aAmerican Visual Culture.  aErotica.  aLatter-day Saints.  aLaw.  aMormon.  aPhotography.  aPolygamy.  aStereoviews.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226410173423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226410173/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles